node.title: Increase of COVID-19 patients in Northern Territory ICUs, as 812 new cases recorded
node.alt: A woman wears a mask and walks in front of street art in the Darwin CBD.
node.description: The Northern Territory now has 114 patients with COVID-19 in hospital, with nine needing oxygen. There' are now five patients in ICUs, an increase from three yesterday.
node.content:
["The Northern Territory today has fewer patients with COVID-19 in hospital, but more\u00a0are in need of oxygen and there has been an increase in the number of people in intensive care.", "There are\u00a0now 114 people in hospital, nine needing oxygen and five in intensive care.", "That's an increase from the three people in the ICU on Sunday, a day where 121 patients with COVID-19 were in Northern Territory hospitals.", "The Territory today reported an additional 812 new cases,\u00a0including 52 who\u00a0have been added to Sunday's total.\u00a0", "Of the 760 in\u00a0Monday's announced daily caseload, 599 came\u00a0from rapid antigen tests.", "Territory-wide, there are\u00a0now about 5,550 active cases of COVID-19.", "Monday's COVID-19 update has been provided via a media release.", "", "
The Territory-wide outdoor mask mandate was introduced on Saturday.(ABC News: Che Chorley)
", "There were 528 cases recorded in the Top End, 86 in Central Australia, 45 in East Arnhem, 16 in the Big Rivers region and 13 in the Barkly.", "At\u00a02pm Sunday, seven-day \"lock-ins\" came into effect in the remote communities of Ampilatwatja, Palumpa, Milingimbi, Milikapiti, Elcho Island, including Galiwin'ku, and the Wessell Islands.", "Today, 27 new cases have been reported in\u00a0Galiwin'ku, three\u00a0in\u00a0Milingimbi and one in Palumpa.", "There's also a Territory-wide, seven-day\u00a0outdoor mask mandate in place, which was introduced on Saturday.", "People in the Northern Territory\u00a0are also required to wear masks indoors, a health measure\u00a0introduced on New Year's Eve.", "", "
I've had COVID, can I get it again?
"]
